Commentary Text: Chakravarthy to Ruturaj Gaikwad, out Caught by Cummins!! Flat and straight down Cummins' throat at deep mid-wicket, a much needed wicket for KKR as du Plessis pats Ruturaj on his back - flighted delivery outside off, Ruturaj had to drag the slog-sweep to the on-side, nailed the shot, but didn't get the elevation needed - went hard and straight at Cummins, who judged it pretty superbly and held on to a good catch. A superb hand from Ruturaj though, has set-up what definitely looks like a 200+ score for CSK. Ruturaj Gaikwad c Cummins b Chakravarthy 64(42) [4s-6 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Thakur to Cummins, out Prasidh Run Out!! 1 run completed. Prasidh has been run out. Third umpire has been called to check but he's well short. A heroic effort from KKR's lower-order doesn't have a fairytale finish as CSK hold on. Low full toss, Cummins spoons it off the toe-end over the bowler. He could've decided to turn down the runs, but Cummins decides there's a chance for two. One isn't an option. But the second is suicidal. Even with the throw being well wide of the stumps, Thakur manages to gather and then swipe as Prasidh is yards short. Prasidh run out (Chahar/Thakur) 0(1)
